<p>The act of sending a condolence message is more than just a formality; it's a demonstration of love, respect, and support.  A carefully chosen message can offer comfort, remind the bereaved of cherished memories, and acknowledge the profound impact of their loss. Whether handwritten, emailed, or delivered through a card, your message should be sincere, thoughtful, and reflect the depth of your sympathy.  Avoid overly formal language and focus on conveying your heartfelt feelings in a genuine and personal manner.</p>
    

